# Dependency / Toolchain Review

I reviewed the whole repo surface: manifests, lockfile, build/deploy scripts, Docker/compose, runtime source, tests, and config. I found 3 confirmed issues, 1 likely cleanup item, and 1 manual-validation risk.

## Confirmed issues

### 1. Storage backend support is present in code but not wired into runtime I/O
- Severity: High
- Evidence: [apps/web/src/lib/storage/index.ts:8-13](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/lib/storage/index.ts#L8-L13), [apps/web/src/lib/storage/index.ts:35-70](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/lib/storage/index.ts#L35-L70), [apps/web/src/lib/storage/index.ts:116-176](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/lib/storage/index.ts#L116-L176), [apps/web/src/app/[locale]/admin/(protected)/settings/settings-client.tsx:22-175](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/app/%5Blocale%5D/admin/(protected)/settings/settings-client.tsx#L22-L175), [apps/web/src/app/actions/settings.ts:14-125](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/app/actions/settings.ts#L14-L125), [apps/web/src/lib/process-image.ts:12-59](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/lib/process-image.ts#L12-L59), [apps/web/src/lib/serve-upload.ts:32-112](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/lib/serve-upload.ts#L32-L112), [apps/web/src/lib/upload-paths.ts:11-46](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/lib/upload-paths.ts#L11-L46), [apps/web/package.json:23-24](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/package.json#L23-L24)
- Failure scenario: the app always writes, processes, and serves files through local filesystem paths even though the storage module exposes `local|minio|s3`. An operator can believe backend switching works, but uploads and serving still bypass the abstraction, so S3/MinIO credentials and AWS SDK deps only gate a code path that is never reached.
- Fix: either wire `getStorage()` into upload/processing/serve paths and add a real admin setting that drives `switchStorageBackend()`, or remove the storage abstraction and its S3/MinIO deps until the integration is complete.
- Confidence: high

### 2. Repo-tracked deploy env hardcodes the live target and is loaded by default
- Severity: High
- Evidence: [.env.deploy:1-5](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/.env.deploy#L1-L5), [scripts/deploy-remote.sh:4-5](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/scripts/deploy-remote.sh#L4-L5), [scripts/deploy-remote.sh:22-63](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/scripts/deploy-remote.sh#L22-L63), [apps/web/deploy.sh:4-30](=/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/deploy.sh#L4-L30)
- Failure scenario: `npm run deploy` will pick up the tracked root `.env.deploy` by default and SSH to the live host/path encoded in the file. That makes a fresh checkout or a new contributor session capable of deploying to production unintentionally.
- Fix: delete the committed `.env.deploy`, keep only `.env.deploy.example`, and make the helper require an explicitly provided local file or an explicit override before it will run.
- Confidence: high

### 3. Production URL defaults can leak localhost into metadata, sitemap, and robots
- Severity: High
- Evidence: [apps/web/src/site-config.json:1-11](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/site-config.json#L1-L11), [apps/web/package.json:10-11](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/package.json#L10-L11), [apps/web/Dockerfile:34-36](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/Dockerfile#L34-L36), [apps/web/src/lib/constants.ts:11-14](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/lib/constants.ts#L11-L14), [apps/web/src/lib/data.ts:766-786](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/lib/data.ts#L766-L786), [apps/web/src/app/[locale]/layout.tsx:15-36](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/app/%5Blocale%5D/layout.tsx#L15-L36), [apps/web/src/app/robots.ts:13-20](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/app/robots.ts#L13-L20), [apps/web/src/app/sitemap.ts:12-45](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/src/app/sitemap.ts#L12-L45), [apps/web/deploy.sh:21-24](/Users/hletrd/flash-shared/gallery/apps/web/deploy.sh#L21-L24)
- Failure scenario: the committed `site-config.json` already points at `http://localhost:3000`, and the build/deploy paths silently accept it if operators do not replace the file. That propagates localhost canonical URLs into metadata, OG tags, sitemap entries, and robots output, which breaks SEO and share links in production.
